<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3897701>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Tyrannosaurus rex (YPM VPPU 016516) right anterior dentary fragment from the Bighorn basin of Wyoming,USA.A, lateral.B, medial.C, dorsal.D, ventral. E, anterior. A1–E1, interpretive drawings of the dentary fragment. Abbreviations: ab, convex articular brace “chin” on the dentary symphysis; alv, alveolus; alvr, alveolar row of foramina; gdl, groove for dental lamina; idp, interdental plates; fio, foramen intermandibularis oralis; ip, inflection point where anterior and ventral margins of dentary meet; lb, lingual bar; mg, Meckelian groove; rim, sinuous rim continuing anterodorsally from articular brace of symphysis; ids, interdentary symphysis; rs, rugose surface; t, tooth; ventr, ventral row of foramina." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3897701/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3897703>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Examples of an adult Tyrannosaurus rex dentaries from the Hell Creek Formation Upper Cretaceous (Maastrichtian) of North America. AMNH FR 5027 from Dry Creek, McCone County, Montana. BHI 3033 from the Niemi Ranch, near Buffalo, Harding County, South Dakota. A, lateral. B, medial. All photographs by Lawrence Witmer; used with permission." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3897703/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3897705>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5.Pedal phalanx II-2 YPM VP 057488(A) of Tyrannosaurus rex from the Upper Cretaceous (Maastrichtian) Buck Creek of Wyoming, USA. A, lateral view. B, medial view. C, dorsal view. D, ventral view. E, posterior view. F, anterior view. G, position of pedal phalanx II-2 in the foot (left foot). Abbreviation: lp, lateral ligament pit." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3897705/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3897707>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Examples of the pedal phalanx II-2 of adult Tyrannosaurus rex (FMNH PR 2081) from the Hell Creek Formation Upper Cretaceous (Maastrichtian) of South Dakota, USA. A, dorsal view. B, ventral view. C, lateral view. Abbreviation: lp, lateral ligament pit. Pedal phalanx II-2 redrawn from Brochu (2003)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3897707/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3897709>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Pedal phalanx III-2 YPM VP 057488(B) of Tyrannosaurus rex from the Upper Cretaceous (Maastrichtian) Buck Creek of Wyoming, USA.A, lateral view.B, medialview.C, dorsal view.D, ventral view.E, posterior view. F, anterior view. G, position of pedal phalanx III-2 in the foot (left foot).Abbreviation: lp, lateral ligament pit." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3897709/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3897711>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Examples of the pedal phalanx III-2 of adult Tyrannosaurus rex (FMNH PR 2081) from the Hell Creek Formation Upper Cretaceous (Maastrichtian) of South Dakota, USA. A, lateral view. B, dorsal view. C, ventral view. Abbreviation: lp, lateral ligament. Pedal phalanx III-2 redrawn from Brochu (2003)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3897711/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

